Crafted to add unique style to any living space, Costa del Sol exemplifies the love of European design. With warm finishes and artistic distressing, each piece offers authenticity on a grand scale and will be something you are proud to pass on to the generations to come. Costa del Sol offers the lifestyle you were meant for. Rustic pecan and white ash burl veneers are paired with rustic maple solids showcasing the aura of fine craftsmanship that is implicit in every design. Conveying authenticity with the hand-rubbed black finish to the mix of glass, hand forged iron, and leather-wrapped cases, this collection makes a statement. Grand in size and demeanor, Costa del Sol expresses its origins through a variety of aging techniques - rasp, rock, worm hole, hand-scoring and chiseling -all of which lend the loving looks of years passed. Coupled with the rustic black finish, melding darkened edges and straw highlights, the collection's aesthetic is inescapably one of warmth and emotion. Of course, it is the smallest details that make the biggest statement. Costa del Sol recognizes this as well. From a grand bail and rosette, to a door knocker and knobs, each replete with Spanish influences, the accents on each design speak to the collection's deepest belief - that your lifestyle awaits amidst Costa del Sol's distinctive villa-inspired world.

description.832: The Four Hands Magnolia dining and occasional table collection is a fresh take on an elegantly designed dining or entry table. Crafted of Mango wood, the table has a raw, white wash finish that is created through sandblasting the wood. The beautiful white wash finish gives an illusion of marble which only adds to the classic sophistication of the Magnolia shapes.
description.833: The Parsons Dining Table, an iconic design from the 1930's, brings classic, modernist design to your home. This piece is hand made by craftsmen following smart design techniques in shop in Brooklyn, New York, minimizing waste by efficient use of resources, therefore passing the manufacturer direct savings to you.
description.834: ''The underside of typical chairs and tables makes a confusing, unrestful world,'' said esteemed Finnish designer Eero Saarinen. ''I wanted to clear up the slum of legs.'' Thus in 1957 Saarinen unveiled his ground-breaking collection of pedestal coffee, dining and side tables, whose simple elegance has endured for 50 years. Stylish and modern, the Saarinen Oval Dining Table is a design masterpiece that fits seamlessly into any environment. Eero Saarinen might be considered by some to be a purist when it came to his approach towards architecture and interior design. He sought the essential idea and reduced it to the most effective structural solution within an overall unity of design. When he designed his pedestal collection, including the Oval Dining Table, Saarinen realized his ideal of formal unity: ''Every significant piece of furniture from the past has a holistic structure.'' To celebrate the 50th anniversary of Saarinen's revolutionary Tulip Collection, Knoll has introduced a reintroduced teak and rosewood tabletop finishes.
description.838: Dining table with an understated style that draws from the beauty of natural materials and combines it with an edgy industrial profile, this piece is sure to bring a timeless look to any dining space. This piece showcases a robust wooden construction for long-lasting quality, with its rectangular table top resting upon sturdy block legs. The lends an earthy luster.
description.839: The round table top of the Adamo Dining table is complemented by the dynamic visual of sleek straight lines intersecting in the pedestal. It is made from solid pine wood, and concrete.

description.849: The Sylvia Dining Room Table features thick, beveled insert top glass and a metal base that is finished in an antiqued silver wash. The traditional styling elements are made fresh by the vintage "found item" vintage finish.

description.854: The Glacier Country Collection features a truly unique finish reminiscent of the Grand Lodges of the Rockies, circa 1900. description.858: Designed to be loved and enjoyed, the timeless quality of River House welcomes the bustling activities of real family life. description.960: This Arts and Crafts-inspired Hudson collection bed will compliment any bedroom. Clean, simple lines, this piece is built using solid wood and select veneers. description.963: Stone County Ironwork's signature Pine collection is a stunning example of nature's detail expressed through exquisite craftsmanship. This table is finished in Hand Rubbed Bronze, which is by far the most popular way to highlight the natural bark textures and the hand-made pine cones.
description.966: Consider this symphony of ovals. The softly rounded chairs are upholstered in gray vinyl, and the wood is finished in darkest ebony. The table boasts a tempered glass, sand blasted insert with a frosted circular pattern.

description.969: For those who love good design and aren't afraid to break a few rules, New Bohemian is a cohesive mix of elements, shapes and textures. Straightforward traditional silhouettes, heavy moldings and exquisitely framed door and drawer fronts provide a backdrop for a unique combination of materials, motifs and details. description.984: Combining the clean, unadorned lines of the International Modernists with organic and geometric forms, the Catalina Collection is suggestive of the works of America's Mid-Century Modern designers. The years following WWII were a time of uncertainty but also of great hope and progress. Designs of the period reflected that sense of hope and the promise of an ideal future. In the Copeland Furniture current period, one finds comfort and nostalgia in Catalina' s retro-modern shapes and sensibilities. Catalina Dining items are finished with a low sheen (10 sheen) top coat. Extension tables incorporate self equalizing, ball bearing extension glides and a single self storing butterfly leaf for single handed operation.
description.985: Unique white aluminum legs an extra light white glass top with radial angles with 2 extensions. Julia is a rectangular expandable table. Structure glossy white with top extra light white glass.
description.988: The Titus Dining table has as antiqued finish base and bamboo wood top. This rectangular shape is perfectly matched with The new Elio double bench for restaurant / bar communal or family dining.
description.989: This Carmel round table offers a timeless design and is made with premium North American reclaimed wood. The finish applied is an antique white or grey multilayer patina that lets the beauty and natural color of the wood be shown. Use this table in a sun room or anywhere else in the home. The built-in groove around the wood frame expands, allowing the table to easily handle variations in temperature and humidity. Available in three different widths, pick one to fit any size room. The round shape makes it easy to converse with family and friends seated around it.
description.990: The Metro dining collection by Diamond Sofa provides an architectural presentation of form and function. A stunning presentation is the result. Perfect for dining and home office applications, the iron base provides the structural integrity for this massive piece of glass.
description.991: The synergy dining table features a rectangular tabletop made with 10 mm tempered smoked glass. Beveled edges provide safety from the corners and create a graceful design. description.994: Very Contemporary Extendable table with painted metal structure.
description.996: Stylish and chic, the Baccarat dining table features a detailed laser-cut crocodile textured body with a black gloss lacquer finish. The table top is treated to reduce damage from scratches and spills. Stunning crystal legs add sophistication to the design. Pictured with the Charlotte velour dining chair. Matches the Baccarat line from the A&X; collection.
description.1005: The Marseille collection provides a perfect solution to transitional dining with clean, classic, well scaled lines. The Marseille dining table features a rich, merlot cherry finish with squared corners, shaped legs and detailed molding. With the 18" leaf in place and will comfortably seat 6.
description.1006: In the midst of the modern design movement in the 1960s, Warren Platner turned a simple concept  transforming steel wire into a unique and supremely modern sculptural furniture collection  into a creative masterpiece: the Platner Table series. This classic table will surely make quite a statement as the focal point of your dining room. The Design Designed in 1966, the Platner Dining Table is truly a unique piece. Considered by many to be a design icon of the modern era, the Platner Table's harmonious forms are created by welding curved vertical steel wire rods to circular frames, producing a moir acute; effect. Decorative, gentle and graceful, the Platner Dining Table is truly one of a kind. An elegant latecomer to the mid-century modern movement, this table works in virtually limitless settings thanks to a diverse array of tabletop options. A bronzed glass top option has been added to further expand its applications. Design Year: 1966. Order with Confidence: Sustainability Statement: Sustainable design is a key component of environmental focus. Commitment to social responsibility and a healthy environment has prompted the company to further articulate its longstanding environmental programs and, with encouragement and support from colleagues in the industry, has re-energized its focus on such ''green'' initiatives as life cycle analysis and LEED® certification. Proud to have contributed to projects that have received LEED certification from the U.S. Green Building Council. Platner Tables with clear glass or natural marble tabletops are Greenguard certified. Products are guaranteed to be free from defects in materials and workmanship during the applicable warranty period set forth in the warranty. Each authentic product includes a certificate of authenticity.
description.1007: How can you help but think of the sea when gazing upon the Seascape Table Its name merely reflects what the shell-like curve of its top and its flowing, curved legs state implicitly--this table is of the sea. Every line undulates like the waves and begs you to follow beyond the horizon. The Seascape Table provides a dramatic dining option.

Product Care:  Wood furniture should never be exposed to extreme heat, humid conditions such as being placed next to A/C or heating outlets or open windows.  It is also best to avoid direct sunlight for this may fade certain finishes. Please always keep in mind that wood breaths and absorbs moisture. Chemicals such as nail polish, nail polish remover, alcohol (rubbing and drinking kind) and even water may leave marks if not attended to immediately. To prevent damage always use protective pads under drinks, hot plates and clean up spills quickly with a soft slightly damp cloth in the direction of the wood grain. Do not place plastic, rubber or other objects on wood furniture for this may discolor finish. Always use felt, cork or leather under any accessories. Cleaning should be done on a weekly basis to remove dust by using a soft cloth in the direction of the wood grain. A high quality, non-silicone furniture polish can also be used. Always avoid oily polishes and waxes. A more through cleaning should be done bi annually by washing with a mild soap that is intended for furniture care and please follow their directions carefully. Do not wash wood tops (bar surfaces, table tops, etc.) with wet rags or other materials and allow product to air dry. This will damage wood and wood veneers and void all warranties. Please remember liquid in glass, cups, or center pieces can sweat leaving ring marks on wood surfaces. This will not be covered under our warranty.  Always keep wood surfaces dry and use protective mats under said items.

Product Care:  Wood furniture should never be exposed to extreme heat, humid conditions such as being placed next to A/C or heating outlets or open windows.  It is also best to avoid direct sunlight for this may fade certain finishes. Please always keep in mind that wood breaths and absorbs moisture. Chemicals such as nail polish, nail polish remover, alcohol (rubbing and drinking kind) and even water may leave marks if not attended to immediately. To prevent damage always use protective pads under drinks, hot plates and clean up spills quickly with a soft slightly damp cloth in the direction of the wood grain. Do not place plastic, rubber or other objects on wood furniture for this may discolor finish. Always use felt, cork or leather under any accessories. Cleaning should be done on a weekly basis to remove dust by using a soft cloth in the direction of the wood grain. A high quality, non-silicone furniture polish can also be used. Always avoid oily polishes and waxes. A more thorough cleaning should be done bi annually by washing with a mild soap that is intended for furniture care and please follow their directions carefully. Do not wash wood tops (bar surfaces, table tops, etc.) with wet rags or other materials and allow product to air dry. This will damage wood and wood veneers and void all warranties. Please remember liquid in glass, cups, or center pieces can sweat leaving ring marks on wood surfaces. This will not be covered under our warranty.  Always keep wood surfaces dry and use protective mats under said items.
